      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="can-incomplete-schema-hurt-my-ai-visibility"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. A 2026 empirical study of 730 AI citations found that generic, partially-filled schema produces an 18-percentage-point citation penalty compared to having no schema at all. AI engines interpret incomplete schema as a mismatch between what you claim and what you deliver. Either implement schema completely or do not implement it at all.</p></div></div>
